==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰeydʰ-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|abiden}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ābīdan||to abide, wait, remain, delay, remain behind; survive; wait for, await; expect}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*uzbīdaną||to expect, tolerate}}, equivalent to {{prefix|en|a|bide}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|abyde||to abide, remain}}, {{cog|gmh|erbīten||to await, expect}}, {{cog|got|𐌿𐍃𐌱𐌴𐌹𐌳𐌰𐌽||to expect, await, have patience}}. The sense of ''pay for'' is due to influence from {{m|en|aby}}.<ref>{{R:MW3 1976|page=3}}</ref>

